{{clipping|en|turkeycock|turkey-cock}} and {{m|en|turkey-hen}}, originally denoting the [[guinea fowl]], an African bird that was first imported to Europe through [[Turkey]]. The word was then transferred to the superficially similar North American bird {{taxfmt|Meleagris gallopavo|species}}.<ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=''n.''{{sup|2}}|noformat=1|id=207632|date=1915|nodot=1}}; {{R:Lexico|alt=turkey{{sup|1}}|pos=n}}</ref>

