===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|ies<l:obsolete>}}

# {{lb|en|countable|originally, now|_|obsolete}} The [[guinea fowl]] ([[family]] {{taxfmt|Numididae|family}}). {{defdate|from c. 1600}}
# {{senseid|en|Q26844}}{{lb|en|countable}} A [[bird#Noun|bird]] in the [[genus]] {{taxfmt|Meleagris|genus}} with a [[fan#Noun|fan]]-[[shaped#Adjective|shaped]] [[tail#Noun|tail]] and [[wattled#Adjective|wattled]] [[neck#Noun|neck]], especially the [[wild turkey]] ({{taxfmt|Meleagris gallopavo|species}}, now [[domesticated#Adjective|domesticated]]).
#* {{RQ:Dickens Christmas Carol|page=157|passage=It ''was'' a '''Turkey'''! He never could have stood upon his legs, that bird. He would have snapped 'em short off in a minute, like sticks of sealing-wax.}}
# {{senseid|en|Q4200953}}{{lb|en|uncountable}} The [[flesh]] or [[meat]] of this bird [[eat#Verb|eaten]] as [[food]].
#: {{ux|en|All week after Thanksgiving, I had '''turkey''' sandwiches for lunch.}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} ''With a distinguishing word'': a bird [[resemble|resembling]] the {{taxfmt|Meleagris gallopavo|species}} (for example, the [[brush turkey]] or [[bush turkey]] ({{taxfmt|Alectura lathami|species}}), and the [[water turkey]] ({{taxfmt|Anhinga anhinga|species}})).
# {{lb|en|countable|bowling}} An [[act#Noun|act]] of [[throw#Verb|throwing]] [[three]] [[strike#Noun|strikes]] [[in a row]].
# {{lb|en|countable|medicine|slang|derogatory}} A [[patient#Noun|patient]] [[feign]]ing [[symptom]]s; a person [[fake#Verb|faking]] [[illness]] or [[injury]]; a [[malingerer]].
#* {{quote-book|en|author=Stephen Charles Frankel|title=Emergency Medical Care in an Urban Area|series=Ph.D. dissertation in Anthropology|location=Berkeley, Calif.|publisher=w:University of California, Berkeley|year=1976|page=118|oclc=21712529|passage=Mumford (1970) noted that the terms ‘crock’, ‘gomer’, and ‘'''turkey'''’, were sometimes utilized by interns to designate different types of undesirable patients, and sometimes used synonymously.|brackets=on}}
# {{lb|en|countable|Australia|US|slang|dated}} A [[pack#Noun|pack]] [[carry|carried]] by a [[lumberman]]; a [[bindle]]; also, a large [[travel bag]], a [[suitcase]]. {{defdate|from early 20th c.}}
# {{lb|en|countable|US|slang}} A [[failure]].
#: {{synonyms|en|flop}}
#: {{ux|en|That film was a '''turkey'''.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=8 Aug 81|journal=Gay Community News|page=11|author=Rob Schmieder|title=Starring Bowie and Berlin|text=And despite the gross incompetence of Hemmings' direction, the ludicrous script, and the heavy-handed acting, there remains a stellar reason to see and enjoy ''Just a Gigolo'': David Bowie. David Bowie is a great actor, and not even this '''turkey''' can obscure that fact.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2021 April 7|author=Christian Wolmar|title=Electrification is a given... but comfort matters as well|journal=RAIL|issue=928|page=46|text=There were a few '''turkeys'''. In the rush to present a futuristic vision, the railways' heritage was largely forgotten and we ended up with new stations at Euston and at Coventry, its brash sidekick which I particularly loathe, although (of course) it won design awards.}}
# {{lb|en|countable|US|slang|usually|mildly|derogatory}} A [[foolish]] or [[inept]] [[person]].
